SIMPLE: supper
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Supper
<hw>Sup"per</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>soper</ets>,
<ets>super</ets>, OF. <ets>super</ets>, <ets>soper</ets>, F.
<ets>souper</ets>; originally an infinitive, to sup, take a meal. See
<er>Soup</er>, and cf. <er>Sup</er> to take supper.]</ety> <def>A meal
taken at the close of the day; the evening meal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Supper</xex> is much used in an obvious sense,
either adjectively or as the first part of a compound; as,
<xex>supper</xex> time or <xex>supper</xex>-time, <xex>supper</xex>
bell, <xex>supper</xex> hour, etc.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supper</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Supper
<hw>Sup"per</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To take supper; to sup.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supper</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Supper
<hw>Sup"per</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To supply with supper.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Kester was <xex>suppering</xex> the
horses.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Mrs. Gaskell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supperless</ent>⟦br⟧
